# =========================================================================
# VSTEP Writing Lab — API Tests (.http)
# Tip: Use "REST Client" extension in VS Code or Visual Studio's built-in HTTP client.
# =========================================================================

@Host = http://localhost:5288
@AuthService = {{Host}}/api/auth
@ExamV2 = {{Host}}/api/v2/ExamPrompts
@GradingV2 = {{Host}}/api/v2/Grading

# 1. AUTHENTICATION & SYNC
# Note: You typically need a real Firebase ID token for these.
# You can get one from the browser console `await auth.currentUser.getIdToken()`

### Sync Firebase User
POST {{AuthService}}/sync
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_ID_TOKEN

{
  "token": "YOUR_FIREBASE_ID_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Complete Onboarding
PUT {{AuthService}}/onboarding
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_ID_TOKEN

{
  "userUid": "USER_UID_HERE",
  "displayName": "Test Student",
  "currentLevel": "B1",
  "targetLevel": "B2"
}

###

# 2. EXAMS & PROMPTS

### Get All Active Exams
GET {{ExamV2}}
Accept: application/json

### Get Exam Outline (Guided Mode Planning)
# Replace {id} with a valid exam ID from the list above
GET {{ExamV2}}/EMAIL_EXAM_001/outline
Accept: application/json

###

# 3. AI GRADING

### Submit Essay for AI Grading (Direct Result)
POST {{GradingV2}}/grade
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_ID_TOKEN

{
  "userUid": "USER_UID_HERE",
  "promptId": "EMAIL_EXAM_001",
  "content": "Dear Sir or Madam, I am writing to inquire about the position of...",
  "taskType": "task1"
}

###

# 4. LEGACY / UTILITY (If needed)

### Get Legacy Question
GET {{Host}}/api/questions/TEST_Q_001
Accept: application/json
